label.value: BUB1B:APC:EB1 complex (frog)

label.value: mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta CDK1- and PLK1-phosphorylated form

value.value: A mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta that has been phosphorylated at one or more CDK1 and PLK1 consensus sites. The phosphorylation at CDK1 site(s) is necessary for the phosphorylation at the PLK1 site(s) to occur. Example: UniProtKB:O60566, Thr-620, MOD:00047|(Ser-676, MOD:00046 and/or Thr-680, MOD:00047)|(Thr-792, MOD:00047 and/or Thr-1008, MOD:00047).

label.value: mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta phosphorylated 2 (human)

value.value: A mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta CDK1- and PLK1-phosphorylated form in human that has had Thr-620 phosphorylated by CDK1, and Ser-676 and/or Thr-680 phosphorylated by PLK1. Additionally, Thr-792 and/or Thr-1008 may be phosphorylated based on in vitro experiments. Example: UniProtKB:O60566-1, Thr-620, MOD:00047|(Ser-676, MOD:00046 and/or Thr-680, MOD:00047)|(Thr-792, MOD:00047 and/or Thr-1008, MOD:00047).

definition.value: Category=organism-modification. Note: This phosphorylated form is observed during pro metaphase, spindle depolymerization (nocodazole), and lack of kinetochore tension (taxol). Kinase=("CDK1"; PR:000003271; Thr-620). Kinase=("PLK1"; PR:P53350; Ser-676/Thr-680).

UniProtKB:Q8JGT8, Thr-605, MOD:00047|MOD:00696.

definition.value: Category=organism-modification. Kinase=("PLK1"; PR:P70032; sites not reported). Kinase=("complex:cyclinB/Cdk1"; PR:000029190; Thr-605).

label.value: mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta phosphorylated 4 (human)

value.value: A mitotic checkpoint serine/threonine-protein kinase BUB1 beta phosphorylated 4 in human. This phosphorylated form is observed in prophase, prometaphase, metaphase, anaphase, spindle depolymerization (nocodazole). This form is not observed when there is a lack of kinetochore tension (taxol). Ser-435, Ser-574 and Ser-720 could also be phosphorylated. Example: UniProtKB:O60566-1, Ser-543/Ser-670/Ser-1043, MOD:00046.
